Quantum Computing Research Paper
Title:
Quantum Optimization for Aircraft Route Planning & Fuel Efficiency

Abstract:

Aircraft route planning and airline operations involve complex optimization problems that significantly impact fuel consumption, operational efficiency, and environmental sustainability. Traditional classical algorithms often struggle to solve these problems efficiently due to their combinatorial nature and increasing scale. This study explores the application of quantum optimization techniques, particularly the Quantum Approximate Optimization Algorithm (QAOA) and Quadratic Unconstrained Binary Optimization (QUBO) models, in improving aircraft route planning and fuel efficiency.
A review of four research papers highlights how quantum computing can address challenges such as tail assignment, aircraft loading, and route optimization. These approaches leverage quantum superposition and interference to explore large solution spaces more efficiently than classical methods. The findings suggest that quantum algorithms can produce high-quality solutions for small-scale instances and demonstrate strong potential for scalability as quantum hardware advances.
Although current limitations in quantum devices restrict large-scale implementation, hybrid quantum-classical approaches provide promising near-term solutions. Overall, quantum optimization represents a transformative approach for enhancing airline operations by reducing fuel consumption, improving scheduling efficiency, and supporting sustainable aviation practices.


Keywords:
