4. Concepts and Theory:

Qubits
•	A qubit is the basic unit of quantum information, similar to a classical bit. 
•	Unlike classical bits (0 or 1), a qubit can exist in both states simultaneously. 
•	This property allows quantum systems to process multiple possibilities at once, making them powerful for optimization problems. 
Superposition
•	Superposition allows a qubit to be in a combination of states (0 and 1) at the same time. 
•	This enables quantum computers to explore many possible solutions simultaneously. 
•	In route optimization, it helps evaluate multiple flight paths at once. 
Entanglement
•	Entanglement is a quantum property where two or more qubits become interconnected. 
•	The state of one qubit directly affects the state of another, even at a distance. 
•	This helps in solving complex optimization problems by creating strong correlations between variables. 
Quantum Interference
•	Quantum interference is used to enhance correct solutions and suppress incorrect ones. 
•	It plays a key role in guiding the system toward optimal solutions. 
•	This is important in algorithms like QAOA for finding the best route or assignment. 
QAOA (Quantum Approximate Optimization Algorithm)
•	QAOA is a hybrid quantum-classical algorithm used for solving optimization problems. 
•	It works by applying a sequence of quantum operations and optimizing parameters. 
•	In this project, QAOA is used for: 
o	Aircraft route planning 
o	Tail assignment 
o	Cost minimization 
QUBO (Quadratic Unconstrained Binary Optimization)
•	QUBO is a mathematical model used to represent optimization problems. 
•	Problems like scheduling and routing are converted into binary variables with cost functions. 
•	This makes them suitable for quantum algorithms like QAOA. 

Hybrid Quantum-Classical Approach
•	Current quantum computers are limited, so hybrid methods are used. 
•	These approaches combine: 
o	Quantum processing (for exploration) 
o	Classical computing (for optimization and control) 
•	This improves performance and makes solutions practical.
